news.title: Over 122 lakh houses sanctioned so far under PMAY-Urban: Government
news.para: In a statement, the Union Housing and Urban Affairs Ministry said that more than 1 crore houses have been grounded and over 61 lakh houses completed and delivered to the beneficiaries. At a virtual event, HUA Secretary Manoj Joshi urged states and union territories to expedite construction work in their respective regions to fulfil the target of "Housing for All".

news.title: Yes bank-DHFL probe: Bombay HC directs ED to move CBI court to transfer case to PMLA court
news.para: Aggarwal also contested that the defence of the accused is same and if these cases are not tried by the same court, then the defence of the accused shall be opened to opposite party and in the other case, the prosecution shall fulfill the cavity and cover up their case pursuant to the defence disclosed by the Accused in other cases.

news.title: Emaar Properties' CEO detained briefly at Delhi airport
news.para: Amit Jain arrived at Delhi super by flight EK-516 from Dubai on Friday and was detained on the basis of an Look Out Circular, issued by the Punjab police.

news.title: Sebi gives UPI payment option to invest in public issues of REITs, InvITs
news.para: ​The new framework, aimed at further streamlining the process, will be applicable to public issue of units of InvIT and REIT, which opens from August 1, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in two separate circulars.

news.title: Ocean Lifespaces leases one lakh sq ft office space to IndiQube in Chennai
news.para: “We see an immense potential in Chennai especially in micro markets like Guindy. This will be our 4th property in Guindy and 5th in Chennai as a whole. Leveraging technology and providing key enablers like flexibility and scalability,” said Rishi Das, Cofounder IndiQube.

news.title: About 301 acres of patta land acquired for Coimbatore airport expansion
news.para: Once the acquisition of land is completed, the Airport Authority of India (AAI) will take over the land and commence the work on the project.

news.title: Tribeca inks joint development pact for 6.5-acre land parcel in south Pune
news.para: The company is planning to develop a premium residential project with a total 268 apartments on the plot that has development potential of 7.5 lakh sq ft.

news.title: Six industrial plots near upcoming Noida Airport fetch Rs 140 crore in e-auction
news.para: ​The e-auction for the plots, located in the industrial sectors 32 and 33, was conducted by the Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA), which functions under the Uttar Pradesh government, the statement said.

news.title: Crack down on properties flouting building norms: Administration to Jamshedpur NAC
news.para: Jadhav has also asked the JNAC to take action against those who are expanding their existing building structures or constructing additional floors in violation of the state building byelaws.

news.title: All anonymous properties will go to government, says Goa CM
news.para: Elaborating, the CM said that in case there are illegally grabbed properties of Goans who have surrendered Indian citizenship and moved abroad, then the government may also think of taking over these properties.

news.title: Kerala government dilutes tax hike for luxury homes
news.para: While SFC proposed a hike of 50-200% tax, based on area of the house (ranging between 3000 sq ft and 10,000 sq ft and those above), government has revised the recommendation drastically and plans to levy 15% tax for all houses with plinth area over 3000 sq ft.

news.title: Nashik civic body likely to revise property tax for industries
news.para: According to AIMA, the property tax has been increased manifold for the industries in the past three-four years.

news.title: Chandigarh administration pushes for conversion of leasehold properties
news.para: UT adviser Dharam Pal on Thursday met the MHA officers. The administration had recently also written a letter to the MHA for giving in-principle nod for conversion of leasehold properties.

news.title: Mysuru: Muda cites soaring price of land for its inability to develop new layouts
news.para: Consequently, Muda is unable to allot sites to new applicants, and for the past decade, has been pushing for the adoption of a 50-50 site-sharing formula with farmers parting with their land for the layouts.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Vejalpur society gets HC nod for redevelopment
news.para: Justice Sangeeta Vishen permitted Swami Vivekanandnagar Cooperative Housing Society to go for demolition of existing 11 blocks and construction of new buildings for 78 flat owners, out of whom 74 (93.5%) consented for redevelopment.
